 In the past we have made patches that have caused problems for a couple of classes. In particular we have managed to break Bards at almost every turn unintentionally. Due to recent debugging we realized that the class structure Bards were put into was &quot;Hosed&quot; and have since removed them from that group, and it is now used on abilities instead of a class as a whole. With that said, Bards will no longer be broken randomly and without explanation. They, along with other classes, will be broken intentionally and without explanation. <br>
 <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>New Goals for Developers of Everquest</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->:<br>
In the past certain patches screwed over particular classes, either intentionally (Monks) or unintentionally (We'd tell you the list, but its rather long and if you learned your class was broken by mistake you might expect us to fix it). As of April 1st a new reward system has been put into place that promotes developing code that hinders and destroys players abilities to defeat monsters and thus gain xp. Which is why the April 1st patch was cancelled. As soon as the announcement was made the patch that was scheduled was scrapped because it did not coincide with the new objectives. Furthermore, breaking one or two classes a patch was seen as a waste of a patch day. We needed to break as many classes as possible. Not to mention that all of us bought stock in ezBoard and we hope that the sudden surge of postings will cause our stock to go up. <br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>What not to do</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->:<br>
Please don't email us with the specifics of your perceived problem. We as devs who code the way the game works don't know anything about the content of the game. Saying you can't aggro kite in PoS means very little to me. 1. I don't know what aggro kite means, does this have something to do with being angry on a windy day? and 2. PoS? If you think its a piece of @#%$ why are you playing? All your little acronymns are very wierd and we don't spend the time trying to figure out what you mean. We just delete your emails so that we can get to the porn and the male member enhancement ads. <br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>What to do</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->:<br>
Keep playing no matter how bad it gets. Actually we have a new incentive: keep paying for your account but do not play. We have a new system that keeps track of how long you don't log in. Subscribers who keep an account paid up for a year, but do not actually log on during that time will receive a significant reward. Owning multiple accounts and not logging on to any of them can result in substantial gain, give it a try!<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>If you insist on bothering us</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->:<br>
Please respect that our raid time is from 3:00pm Pacific to 12:00 midnight Pacific. We gonna own the Mids tonight! (BTW if you don't know what a &quot;Mid&quot; is you need to check out this cool game called DAoC, now that is a game that isn't broke!) Anyway, if you call during our scheduled raid times we won't be able to help you at all. If you call during the non raid times we might answer, but won't be able to help you. <br>
<br>
Thanks, <br>
SoE Dev Team <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=321100" target="top">Agnol Reyasdemuertes </a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
